The paper discusses cognitive engineering, which involves the design of intelligent systems that can perform tasks that typically require human-like intelligence. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and robotics (cs.RO). Given the focus on cognitive systems and the multi-disciplinary nature of the field, it is likely that the paper could be classified under any of these sub-categories, with cs.HC and cs.AI being the most likely.
